President Obama has declared a major disaster in the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania due to severe storms and flooding that occurred in October 2016. Federal aid will be provided to supplement recovery efforts in the affected areas. Funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Steven S. Ward has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, media should contact the FEMA News Desk.